	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I use <a href="http://humanbalance.net/gale/us/spec.html" class="postlink">GraphicsGale</a> which uses grids, and lets you handle the pallete y any way you like, swapping colors, specifing color indexes, etc. It's very good.
<br />But still, I prefer photoshop to do the drawing, painting, etc. Then export it as PNG with the exact amount of colors I want, then adjust color indexes in GraphicsGale.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


